                                <shortdescription>(for accessibility)</shortdescription>
                            </image>

                            




                            
                        </sidebyside>
                        <p>
                            <m>\bullet</m> What is the name of the above pyramids?
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Measure the edges of the rectangular-based pyramid
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Cut and open the rectangular-based pyramid along the edges to reveal its net as shown below.
                        </p>
                        <image width="70%">
                        <latex-image label="net-of-rectangular-based-pyramid">
                            \begin{tikzpicture}
                                % Base rectangle
                                    \draw[very thick,fill=pink] (0,0) rectangle (8,4);
                                    % Long side triangles
                                    \draw[very thick] (0,0)--(4,-5)--(8,0);
                                    \draw[very thick] (0,4)--(4,9)--(8,4);
                                    % Short side triangles
                                    \draw[very thick] (0,0)--(-4,2)--(0,4);
                                    \draw[very thick] (8,0)--(12,2)--(8,4);
                            \end{tikzpicture}
                        </latex-image>
                            
                        </image>

                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Find the area of each faces of the above net.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Find the surface area of the rectangular-based pyramid using the net.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            What is the surface area of the triangular-based pyramid?
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            What is the surface area of the square-based pyramid?
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            What is the surface area of the pentagonal-based pyramid?
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Repeat the above steps for the triangular-based and square-based pyramids.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Discuss your findings with other group members.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </activity>
        <p>
            <term>Key Takeaway</term>
        </p>
        <p>
            <ol marker="a)">
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <me>\text{Surface Area of Pyramids}=\text{Base Area}+\text{area of thefour triangular faces.}</me>
                    </p>
                     <p>
                        <m>\textbf{Note:}</m>
                    </p>
                    
                    <p>
                        Understanding the <m>\textbf{net}</m> helps visualize and calculate total area easily.
                    </p>
                </li>
                
            </ol>
        </p>
        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Calculate the surface area of the pyramid below.
                </p>
                <image source="/solid.png" width="50%">
                    <shortdescription>The model of a pyramid</shortdescription>
                </image>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    The net of the above model is as shown below.
                </p>
                <image source="/net.png" width="70%">
                    <shortdescription>The model 2</shortdescription>
                </image>
                <p>
                    The base area is <m>8 \times 6 = 48 \text{cm}^2</m>.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The height of the triangular face.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>\text{h}= \amp \sqrt{10^2-3^2} </mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp 9.5394 \, \text{cm}</mrow>
                        
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    The height of triangular face.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>\text{h}= \amp \sqrt{10^2-4^2} </mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp 9.165 \, \text{cm}</mrow>

                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Area of the triangles are as shown:
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>\text{Area}=\frac{1}{2}\times \text{base}\times \text{height}</mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp \frac{1}{2} \times 8 \times 9.165 \times 2</mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp 74.52 \, \text{cm}^2</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>\text{Area}=\frac{1}{2}\times \text{base}\times \text{height}</mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp \frac{1}{2} \times 6 \times 9.5394 \times 2</mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp 57.23 \, \text{cm}^2</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    The total surface area is given by:
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>\text{Total Surface Area}=\text{Base Area}+\text{Area of Triangles}</mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp 48 + 74.52 + 57.23</mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp 179.75 \, \text{cm}^2</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
               <p>
                   Therefore, the total surface area of the pyramid is <m>{\color{black}179.75 \, \text{cm}^2}</m>.
               </p>

            </solution>
        </example>
        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    A tent is shaped like a square-based pyramid. The base is <m>3 \, \text{m}</m> by <m>3 \, \text{m}</m> and
                    each triangular side has a height of <m>2.5 \, \text{m}</m>. Find the amount of canvas needed to make the tent.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    The base area is given by;
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>\text{Base Area} = \text{length} \times \text{width}</mrow>
                        <mrow>= 3 \times 3</mrow>
                        <mrow>= 9 \, \text{m}^2</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    The area of the triangular faces is given by:
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>\text{Area} = \frac{1}{2} \times \text{base} \times \text{height}</mrow>
                        <mrow>= \frac{1}{2} \times 3 \times 2.5 \times 4</mrow>
                        <mrow>= 15 \, \text{m}^2</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Therefore, the total surface area of the tent is <m>{\color{black}24 \, \text{m}^2}</m>.
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Find the area of the figure below:
                </p>
                <image width="50%">
                <latex-image label="exer1">
                    \begin{tikzpicture}
                        % ===== TRIANGULAR PYRAMID MODEL (7 cm edges) =====
                        \begin{scope}[shift={(0,0)}]
                            % Base triangle (equilateral, 7 cm sides)
                            \draw[thick, fill=blue!20] (0,0) -- (7,0) -- (3.5,6.06) -- cycle;
                            
                            % Apex (calculated height for 7 cm edges)
                            \coordinate (apex) at (3.5,2.02);
                            
                            % Edges to apex
                            \draw[very thick] (0,0) -- (apex);
                            \draw[very thick] (7,0) -- (apex);
                            \draw [very thick] (3.5,6.06) -- (apex);
                            
                            % Labels
                            \node[below] at (3.5,-0.3) {7 cm};
                        \end{scope}
                    \end{tikzpicture}
                </latex-image>
                    
                </image>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    The net of the figure is as shown below:
                </p>
                <image width="50%">
                <latex-image label="exer">
                    \begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.8]
                        % --- Base triangle ---
                        \coordinate (A) at (0,0);
                        \coordinate (B) at (7,0);
                        \coordinate (C) at (3.5,6.06); 

                        \draw[very thick, fill=blue!15] (A) -- (B) -- (C) -- cycle;
                        \node at (3.5,-0.4) {\textbf{7 cm}};

                        % --- Side triangle 1 (attached to AB) ---
                        \coordinate (D) at (3.5,-6.06);
                        \draw[very thick, fill=green!15] (A) -- (B) -- (D) -- cycle;

                        % --- Side triangle 2 (attached to AC) ---
                        \coordinate (E) at (-6.06,3.03);
                        \draw[very thick, fill=yellow!20] (A) -- (C) -- (E) -- cycle;

                        % --- Side triangle 3 (attached to BC) ---
                        \coordinate (F) at (10.56,3.03);
                        \draw[very thick, fill=red!20] (B) -- (C) -- (F) -- cycle;

                        % Edge labels (optional, all = 7 cm)
                        \node [left]at (1.75,3.2) {7 cm};
                        \node [right]at (5.25,3.2) {7 cm};
                        \node [below]at (3,0) {7 cm};   
                    \end{tikzpicture}
                </latex-image>
                    
                </image>
                <p>
                    The height of the pyramid is given by:
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow> \text{h}=\amp  \sqrt{7^2-3.5^2}</mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp  \sqrt{49-12.25}</mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp  \sqrt{36.75}</mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp  6.06 \, \text{cm}</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    The area of the pyramid is given by:
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow> \text{A}=\amp  \frac{1}{2} \times 7 \times 6.06</mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp  21.21 \, \text{cm}^2</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    The total area is given by:
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>= \amp  21.21 + 21.21 \times 4</mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp  21.21 + 84.84</mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp  106.05 \, \text{cm}^2</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Therefore, the total surface area of the pyramid is <m>{\color{blue}106.05 \, \text{cm}^2 }</m>.
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
